The thing is that `subscriberContext()` methods were deprecated and removed in 3.5.0

You should use `contextWrite()` and `deferContextual()` instead.

Declare a filter bean like this:

&lt;!-- language: java --&gt;
    @Component
    public class ReactiveRequestContextFilter implements WebFilter {
    
        @Override
        public Mono&lt;Void&gt; filter(ServerWebExchange exchange, WebFilterChain chain) {
            return Mono.deferContextual(contextView -&gt; {
                ServerHttpRequest request = exchange.getRequest();
                return chain.filter(exchange)
                        .contextWrite(context -&gt; context.put(ReactiveRequestContextHolder.CONTEXT_KEY, request));
            });
        }
    }

Your ReactiveRequestContextHolder:

&lt;!-- language: java --&gt;

    public class ReactiveRequestContextHolder {
    
        public static final Class&lt;ServerHttpRequest&gt; CONTEXT_KEY = ServerHttpRequest.class;
    
        public static Mono&lt;ServerHttpRequest&gt; getRequest() {
            return Mono.deferContextual(contextView -&gt; Mono.just(contextView.get(CONTEXT_KEY)));
        }
    }

And your controller, for example:

&lt;!-- language: java --&gt;
    @GetMapping
    public Mono&lt;String&gt; test() {
       return ReactiveRequestContextHolder.getRequest()
               .map(ServerHttpRequest::getId);
    }

