answers.body_markdown:
Here in your case your are not executing the query with `Interface Projection` in a correct way:

The Interface Projection:


    public interface UserCreatedByDate {
    
      String getCreated();
    
      String getCounter();
    
    }

The query in Repository(in my case I tried to check it with Postgresql where function `FROM_UNIXTIME` is not present by the way it is not a problem):

      @Query(value = &quot;SELECT to_char(date(to_timestamp(created_at/1000)), &#39;YYYY-MM-DD&#39;) as created, count(*) as counter from &quot; +
          &quot; profile_entity where title like :title and created_at &gt;= :from and created_at &lt; :to &quot; +
          &quot;group by profile_entity.created_at&quot;,
          nativeQuery = true)
      List&lt;UserCreatedByDate&gt; findCountAllCreatedBetweenGroupByDate(@Param(&quot;from&quot;) Long from,
          @Param(&quot;to&quot;) Long to, @Param(&quot;title&quot;) String title);

After it i got the next one result, that meet 100% your requirements:

[![enter image description here][1]][1]


P.S. The problem was in the repository query(you are using interface projection as DTO projection)


  [1]: https://i.stack.imgur.com/gcOVu.png

